{
  "video_id": "uYyvbgINZkQ",
  "title": "Verna Myers: How to overcome our biases? Walk boldly toward them",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12717.0,
      "end_time": 15167.0,
      "text": "I was on a long road trip this summer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15167.0,
      "end_time": 18245.0,
      "text": "and I was having a wonderful time listening"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18245.0,
      "end_time": 22992.0,
      "text": "to the amazing Isabel Wilkerson&#39;s &quot;The Warmth of Other Suns.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22992.0,
      "end_time": 32761.0,
      "text": "It documents six million black folks fleeing the South from 1915 to 1970"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 32761.000000000004,
      "end_time": 36238.0,
      "text": "looking for a respite from all the brutality"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 36238.0,
      "end_time": 39999.0,
      "text": "and trying to get to a better opportunity up North,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 39999.0,
      "end_time": 44407.0,
      "text": "and it was filled with stories of the resilience and the brilliance"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 44407.0,
      "end_time": 46362.0,
      "text": "of African-Americans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 46362.0,
      "end_time": 50731.0,
      "text": "and it was also really hard to hear all the stories of the horrors"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 50731.0,
      "end_time": 56320.0,
      "text": "and the humility, and all the humiliations."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 56320.0,
      "end_time": 61029.0,
      "text": "It was especially hard to hear about the beatings and the burnings"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 61029.0,
      "end_time": 63366.0,
      "text": "and the lynchings of black men."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 63366.0,
      "end_time": 66632.0,
      "text": "And I said, &quot;You know, this is a little deep."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 66632.0,
      "end_time": 70915.0,
      "text": "I need a break. I&#39;m going to turn on the radio.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 70915.0,
      "end_time": 74061.0,
      "text": "I turned it on, and there it was:"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 74061.0,
      "end_time": 76233.0,
      "text": "Ferguson, Missouri,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 76233.0,
      "end_time": 78445.0,
      "text": "Michael Brown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 78445.0,
      "end_time": 80665.0,
      "text": "18-year-old black man,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 80665.0,
      "end_time": 86564.0,
      "text": "unarmed, shot by a white police officer, laid on the ground dead,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 86564.0,
      "end_time": 90478.0,
      "text": "blood running for four hours"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 90478.0,
      "end_time": 94993.0,
      "text": "while his grandmother and little children and his neighbors watched in horror,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 94993.0,
      "end_time": 98019.0,
      "text": "and I thought,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 98019.0,
      "end_time": 101240.0,
      "text": "here it is again."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 101240.0,
      "end_time": 104962.0,
      "text": "This violence, this brutality against black men"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 104962.0,
      "end_time": 107824.0,
      "text": "has been going on for centuries."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 107824.0,
      "end_time": 112396.0,
      "text": "I mean, it&#39;s the same story. It&#39;s just different names."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 112396.0,
      "end_time": 116498.0,
      "text": "It could have been Amadou Diallo."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 116498.0,
      "end_time": 118823.0,
      "text": "It could have been Sean Bell."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 118823.0,
      "end_time": 122213.0,
      "text": "It could have been Oscar Grant."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 122213.0,
      "end_time": 126205.0,
      "text": "It could have been Trayvon Martin."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 126205.0,
      "end_time": 129044.0,
      "text": "This violence, this brutality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 129044.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131863.0,
      "text": "is really something that&#39;s part of our national psyche."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 131863.0,
      "end_time": 134632.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s part of our collective history."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 134632.0,
      "end_time": 139447.0,
      "text": "What are we going to do about it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 139447.0,
      "end_time": 144672.0,
      "text": "You know that part of us that still crosses the street,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 144672.0,
      "end_time": 146722.0,
      "text": "locks the doors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 146722.0,
      "end_time": 149076.0,
      "text": "clutches the purses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 149076.0,
      "end_time": 151962.0,
      "text": "when we see young black men?"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 151962.0,
      "end_time": 154023.0,
      "text": "That part."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 154023.0,
      "end_time": 157971.0,
      "text": "I mean, I know we&#39;re not shooting people down in the street,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 157971.0,
      "end_time": 162058.0,
      "text": "but I&#39;m saying that the same stereotypes and prejudices"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 162058.0,
      "end_time": 165123.0,
      "text": "that fuel those kinds of tragic incidents"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 165123.0,
      "end_time": 167328.0,
      "text": "are in us."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 167328.0,
      "end_time": 171195.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve been schooled in them as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 171195.0,
      "end_time": 177758.0,
      "text": "I believe that we can stop these types of incidents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 177758.0,
      "end_time": 180729.0,
      "text": "these Fergusons from happening,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 180729.0,
      "end_time": 186078.0,
      "text": "by looking within and being willing to change ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 186078.0,
      "end_time": 189369.0,
      "text": "So I have a call to action for you."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 189369.0,
      "end_time": 193454.0,
      "text": "There are three things that I want to offer us today to think about"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 193454.0,
      "end_time": 198562.0,
      "text": "as ways to stop Ferguson from happening again;"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 198562.0,
      "end_time": 200861.0,
      "text": "three things that I think will help us"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 200861.0,
      "end_time": 204336.0,
      "text": "reform our images of young black men;"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 204336.0,
      "end_time": 208652.0,
      "text": "three things that I&#39;m hoping will not only protect them"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 208652.0,
      "end_time": 212848.0,
      "text": "but will open the world so that they can thrive."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 212848.0,
      "end_time": 215149.0,
      "text": "Can you imagine that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 215149.0,
      "end_time": 219700.0,
      "text": "Can you imagine our country embracing young black men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 219700.0,
      "end_time": 225045.0,
      "text": "seeing them as part of our future, giving them that kind of openness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 225045.0,
      "end_time": 228758.0,
      "text": "that kind of grace we give to people we love?"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 228758.0,
      "end_time": 233054.0,
      "text": "How much better would our lives be? How much better would our country be?"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 233054.0,
      "end_time": 235967.0,
      "text": "Let me just start with number one."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 235967.0,
      "end_time": 240956.0,
      "text": "We gotta get out of denial."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 240956.0,
      "end_time": 243359.0,
      "text": "Stop trying to be good people."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 243359.0,
      "end_time": 245503.0,
      "text": "We need real people."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 245503.0,
      "end_time": 247412.0,
      "text": "You know, I do a lot of diversity work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 247412.0,
      "end_time": 250382.0,
      "text": "and people will come up to me at the beginning of the workshop."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 250382.0,
      "end_time": 254067.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re like, &quot;Oh, Ms. Diversity Lady, we&#39;re so glad you&#39;re here&quot; --"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 254067.0,
      "end_time": 255646.0,
      "text": "(Laughter) --"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 255646.0,
      "end_time": 258659.0,
      "text": "&quot;but we don&#39;t have a biased bone in our body.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 258659.0,
      "end_time": 260522.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m like, &quot;Really?"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 260522.0,
      "end_time": 265010.0,
      "text": "Because I do this work every day, and I see all my biases.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 265010.0,
      "end_time": 268525.0,
      "text": "I mean, not too long ago, I was on a plane"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 268525.0,
      "end_time": 272902.0,
      "text": "and I heard the voice of a woman pilot coming over the P.A. system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 272902.0,
      "end_time": 275014.0,
      "text": "and I was just so excited, so thrilled."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 275014.0,
      "end_time": 278116.0,
      "text": "I was like, &quot;Yes, women, we are rocking it."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 278116.0,
      "end_time": 280326.0,
      "text": "We are now in the stratosphere.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 280326.0,
      "end_time": 283460.0,
      "text": "It was all good, and then it started getting turbulent and bumpy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 283460.0,
      "end_time": 284877.0,
      "text": "and I was like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 284877.0,
      "end_time": 287295.0,
      "text": "&quot;I hope she can drive.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 287295.0,
      "end_time": 288634.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 288634.0,
      "end_time": 289826.0,
      "text": "I know. Right."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 289826.0,
      "end_time": 292068.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not even like I knew that was a bias"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 292068.0,
      "end_time": 295558.0,
      "text": "until I was coming back on the other leg and there&#39;s always a guy driving"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 295558.0,
      "end_time": 297307.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s often turbulent and bumpy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 297307.0,
      "end_time": 300133.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve never questioned the confidence of the male driver."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 300133.0,
      "end_time": 302089.0,
      "text": "The pilot is good."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 302089.0,
      "end_time": 304585.0,
      "text": "Now, here&#39;s the problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 304585.0,
      "end_time": 312096.0,
      "text": "If you ask me explicitly, I would say, &quot;Female pilot: awesome.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 312096.0,
      "end_time": 316792.0,
      "text": "But it appears that when things get funky and a little troublesome, a little risky,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 316792.0,
      "end_time": 320802.0,
      "text": "I lean on a bias that I didn&#39;t even know that I had."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 320802.0,
      "end_time": 323416.0,
      "text": "You know, fast-moving planes in the sky,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 323416.0,
      "end_time": 325379.0,
      "text": "I want a guy."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 325379.0,
      "end_time": 327662.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s my default."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 327662.0,
      "end_time": 330291.0,
      "text": "Men are my default."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 330291.0,
      "end_time": 332611.0,
      "text": "Who is your default?"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 332611.0,
      "end_time": 334641.0,
      "text": "Who do you trust?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 334641.0,
      "end_time": 336774.0,
      "text": "Who are you afraid of?"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 336774.0,
      "end_time": 340805.0,
      "text": "Who do you implicitly feel connected to?"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 340805.0,
      "end_time": 343847.0,
      "text": "Who do you run away from?"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 343847.0,
      "end_time": 346271.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to tell you what we have learned."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 346271.0,
      "end_time": 351669.0,
      "text": "The implicit association test, which measures unconscious bias,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 351669.0,
      "end_time": 353389.0,
      "text": "you can go online and take it."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 353389.0,
      "end_time": 355645.0,
      "text": "Five million people have taken it."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 355645.0,
      "end_time": 361555.0,
      "text": "Turns out, our default is white. We like white people."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 361555.0,
      "end_time": 364315.0,
      "text": "We prefer white. What do I mean by that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 364315.0,
      "end_time": 369569.0,
      "text": "When people are shown images of black men and white men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 369569.0,
      "end_time": 373562.0,
      "text": "we are more quickly able to associate"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 373562.0,
      "end_time": 377640.0,
      "text": "that picture with a positive word, that white person with a positive word,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 377640.0,
      "end_time": 380305.0,
      "text": "than we are when we are trying to associate"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 380305.0,
      "end_time": 384010.0,
      "text": "positive with a black face, and vice versa."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 384010.0,
      "end_time": 385900.0,
      "text": "When we see a black face,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 385900.0,
      "end_time": 391948.0,
      "text": "it is easier for us to connect black with negative"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 391948.0,
      "end_time": 394075.0,
      "text": "than it is white with negative."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 394075.0,
      "end_time": 401039.0,
      "text": "Seventy percent of white people taking that test prefer white."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 401039.0,
      "end_time": 405753.0,
      "text": "Fifty percent of black people taking that test prefer white."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 405753.0,
      "end_time": 411310.0,
      "text": "You see, we were all outside when the contamination came down."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 411310.0,
      "end_time": 417697.0,
      "text": "What do we do about the fact that our brain automatically associates?"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 417697.0,
      "end_time": 423306.0,
      "text": "You know, one of the things that you probably are thinking about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 423306.0,
      "end_time": 425284.0,
      "text": "and you&#39;re probably like, you know what,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 425284.0,
      "end_time": 428818.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m just going to double down on my color blindness."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 428818.0,
      "end_time": 430545.0,
      "text": "Yes, I&#39;m going to recommit to that."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 430545.0,
      "end_time": 432662.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to suggest to you, no."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 432662.0,
      "end_time": 435821.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve gone about as far as we can go trying to make a difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 435821.0,
      "end_time": 437434.0,
      "text": "trying to not see color."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 437434.0,
      "end_time": 442269.0,
      "text": "The problem was never that we saw color. It was what we did when we saw the color."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 442269.0,
      "end_time": 446270.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a false ideal."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 446270.0,
      "end_time": 449040.0,
      "text": "And while we&#39;re busy pretending not to see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 449040.0,
      "end_time": 452871.0,
      "text": "we are not being aware of the ways in which racial difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 452871.0,
      "end_time": 458152.0,
      "text": "is changing people&#39;s possibilities, that&#39;s keeping them from thriving,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 458152.0,
      "end_time": 463339.0,
      "text": "and sometimes it&#39;s causing them an early death."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 463339.0,
      "end_time": 468885.0,
      "text": "So in fact, what the scientists are telling us is, no way."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 468885.0,
      "end_time": 471280.0,
      "text": "Don&#39;t even think about color blindness."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 471280.0,
      "end_time": 473760.0,
      "text": "In fact, what they&#39;re suggesting is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 473760.0,
      "end_time": 478290.0,
      "text": "stare at awesome black people."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 478290.0,
      "end_time": 480030.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 480030.0,
      "end_time": 484997.0,
      "text": "Look at them directly in their faces and memorize them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 484997.0,
      "end_time": 489663.0,
      "text": "because when we look at awesome folks who are black,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 489663.0,
      "end_time": 492872.0,
      "text": "it helps to dissociate"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 492872.0,
      "end_time": 498405.0,
      "text": "the association that happens automatically in our brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 498405.0,
      "end_time": 503827.0,
      "text": "Why do you think I&#39;m showing you these beautiful black men behind me?"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 503827.0,
      "end_time": 507039.0,
      "text": "There were so many, I had to cut them."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 507039.0,
      "end_time": 508351.0,
      "text": "Okay, so here&#39;s the thing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 508351.0,
      "end_time": 514279.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m trying to reset your automatic associations about who black men are."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 514279.0,
      "end_time": 516641.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m trying to remind you"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 516640.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521664.99999999994,
      "text": "that young black men grow up to be amazing human beings"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 521664.99999999994,
      "end_time": 527371.0,
      "text": "who have changed our lives and made them better."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 527371.0,
      "end_time": 529890.0,
      "text": "So here&#39;s the thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 529890.0,
      "end_time": 532441.0,
      "text": "The other possibility in science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 532441.0,
      "end_time": 535365.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s only temporarily changing our automatic assumptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 535365.0,
      "end_time": 537870.0,
      "text": "but one thing we know"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 537870.0,
      "end_time": 542662.0,
      "text": "is that if you take a white person who is odious that you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 542662.0,
      "end_time": 545672.0,
      "text": "and stick it up next to a person of color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 545672.0,
      "end_time": 548131.0,
      "text": "a black person, who is fabulous,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 548131.0,
      "end_time": 551637.0,
      "text": "then that sometimes actually causes us to disassociate too."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 551637.0,
      "end_time": 556851.0,
      "text": "So think Jeffrey Dahmer and Colin Powell."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 556851.0,
      "end_time": 559359.0,
      "text": "Just stare at them, right? (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 559359.0,
      "end_time": 562168.0,
      "text": "But these are the things. So go looking for your bias."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 562168.0,
      "end_time": 566257.0,
      "text": "Please, please, just get out of denial and go looking for disconfirming data"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 566257.0,
      "end_time": 570847.0,
      "text": "that will prove that in fact your old stereotypes are wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 570847.0,
      "end_time": 572781.0,
      "text": "Okay, so that&#39;s number one: number two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 572781.0,
      "end_time": 577466.0,
      "text": "what I&#39;m going to say is move toward young black men instead of away from them."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 577466.0,
      "end_time": 580058.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not the hardest thing to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 580058.0,
      "end_time": 583928.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s also one of these things"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 583928.0,
      "end_time": 586604.0,
      "text": "where you have to be conscious and intentional about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 586604.0,
      "end_time": 589712.0,
      "text": "You know, I was in a Wall Street area one time several years ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 589712.0,
      "end_time": 593094.0,
      "text": "when I was with a colleague of mine, and she&#39;s really wonderful"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 593094.0,
      "end_time": 596734.0,
      "text": "and she does diversity work with me and she&#39;s a woman of color, she&#39;s Korean."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 596734.0,
      "end_time": 598684.0,
      "text": "And we were outside, it was late at night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 598684.0,
      "end_time": 601726.0,
      "text": "and we were sort of wondering where we were going, we were lost."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 601726.0,
      "end_time": 605910.0,
      "text": "And I saw this person across the street, and I was thinking, &quot;Oh great, black guy.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 605910.0,
      "end_time": 608678.0,
      "text": "I was going toward him without even thinking about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 608678.0,
      "end_time": 612462.0,
      "text": "And she was like, &quot;Oh, that&#39;s interesting.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 612462.0,
      "end_time": 615280.0,
      "text": "The guy across the street, he was a black guy."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 615280.0,
      "end_time": 618939.0,
      "text": "I think black guys generally know where they&#39;re going."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 618939.0,
      "end_time": 622584.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know why exactly I think that, but that&#39;s what I think."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 622584.0,
      "end_time": 627925.0,
      "text": "So she was saying, &quot;Oh, you were going, &#39;Yay, a black guy&#39;?&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 627925.0,
      "end_time": 630989.0,
      "text": "She said, &quot;I was going, &#39;Ooh, a black guy.&#39;&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 630989.0,
      "end_time": 634385.0,
      "text": "Other direction. Same need, same guy, same clothes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 634385.0,
      "end_time": 637734.0,
      "text": "same time, same street, different reaction."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 637734.0,
      "end_time": 640463.0,
      "text": "And she said, &quot;I feel so bad. I&#39;m a diversity consultant."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 640463.0,
      "end_time": 643281.0,
      "text": "I did the black guy thing. I&#39;m a woman of color. Oh my God!&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 643281.0,
      "end_time": 647055.0,
      "text": "And I said, &quot;You know what? Please. We really need to relax about this.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 647055.0,
      "end_time": 650781.0,
      "text": "I mean, you&#39;ve got to realize I go way back with black guys."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 650781.0,
      "end_time": 653527.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 653527.0,
      "end_time": 656763.0,
      "text": "My dad is a black guy. You see what I&#39;m saying?"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 656763.0,
      "end_time": 660703.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve got a 6&#39;5&quot; black guy son. I was married to a black guy."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 660703.0,
      "end_time": 663219.0,
      "text": "My black guy thing is so wide and so deep"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 663219.0,
      "end_time": 668009.0,
      "text": "that I can pretty much sort and figure out who that black guy is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 668009.0,
      "end_time": 669959.0,
      "text": "and he was my black guy."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 669959.0,
      "end_time": 673733.0,
      "text": "He said, &quot;Yes, ladies, I know where you&#39;re going. I&#39;ll take you there.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 673733.0,
      "end_time": 677376.0,
      "text": "You know, biases are the stories we make up about people"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 677376.0,
      "end_time": 679888.0,
      "text": "before we know who they actually are."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 679888.0,
      "end_time": 682620.0,
      "text": "But how are we going to know who they are"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 682620.0,
      "end_time": 686427.0,
      "text": "when we&#39;ve been told to avoid and be afraid of them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 686427.0,
      "end_time": 691480.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m going to tell you to walk toward your discomfort."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 691480.0,
      "end_time": 694517.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m not asking you to take any crazy risks."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 694517.0,
      "end_time": 699417.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m saying, just do an inventory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 699417.0,
      "end_time": 703309.0,
      "text": "expand your social and professional circles."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 703309.0,
      "end_time": 705139.0,
      "text": "Who&#39;s in your circle?"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 705139.0,
      "end_time": 707635.0,
      "text": "Who&#39;s missing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 707635.0,
      "end_time": 711592.0,
      "text": "How many authentic relationships"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 711592.0,
      "end_time": 718062.0,
      "text": "do you have with young black people, folks, men, women?"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 718062.0,
      "end_time": 721814.0,
      "text": "Or any other major difference from who you are"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 721814.0,
      "end_time": 725150.0,
      "text": "and how you roll, so to speak?"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 725150.0,
      "end_time": 728229.0,
      "text": "Because, you know what? Just look around your periphery."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 728229.0,
      "end_time": 730532.0,
      "text": "There may be somebody at work, in your classroom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 730532.0,
      "end_time": 733980.0,
      "text": "in your house of worship, somewhere, there&#39;s some black young guy there."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 733980.0,
      "end_time": 735438.0,
      "text": "And you&#39;re nice. You say hi."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 735438.0,
      "end_time": 741784.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m saying go deeper, closer, further, and build the kinds of relationships,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 741784.0,
      "end_time": 747064.0,
      "text": "the kinds of friendships that actually cause you to see the holistic person"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 747064.0,
      "end_time": 750552.0,
      "text": "and to really go against the stereotypes."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 750552.0,
      "end_time": 752145.0,
      "text": "I know some of you are out there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 752145.0,
      "end_time": 755436.0,
      "text": "I know because I have some white friends in particular that will say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 755436.0,
      "end_time": 757408.0,
      "text": "&quot;You have no idea how awkward I am."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 757408.0,
      "end_time": 760140.0,
      "text": "Like, I don&#39;t think this is going to work for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 760140.0,
      "end_time": 761876.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m sure I&#39;m going to blow this.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 761876.0,
      "end_time": 767835.0,
      "text": "Okay, maybe, but this thing is not about perfection. It&#39;s about connection."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 767835.0,
      "end_time": 772839.0,
      "text": "And you&#39;re not going to get comfortable before you get uncomfortable."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 772839.0,
      "end_time": 774969.0,
      "text": "I mean, you just have to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 774969.0,
      "end_time": 777316.0,
      "text": "And young black men, what I&#39;m saying is"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 777316.0,
      "end_time": 782361.0,
      "text": "if someone comes your way, genuinely and authentically, take the invitation."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 782361.0,
      "end_time": 784211.0,
      "text": "Not everyone is out to get you."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 784211.0,
      "end_time": 788691.0,
      "text": "Go looking for those people who can see your humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 788691.0,
      "end_time": 792199.0,
      "text": "You know, it&#39;s the empathy and the compassion"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 792199.0,
      "end_time": 796903.0,
      "text": "that comes out of having relationships with people who are different from you."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 796903.0,
      "end_time": 799898.0,
      "text": "Something really powerful and beautiful happens:"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 799898.0,
      "end_time": 802414.0,
      "text": "you start to realize that they are you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 802414.0,
      "end_time": 808196.0,
      "text": "that they are part of you, that they are you in your family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 808196.0,
      "end_time": 811194.0,
      "text": "and then we cease to be bystanders"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 811194.0,
      "end_time": 815179.0,
      "text": "and we become actors, we become advocates,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 815179.0,
      "end_time": 817677.0,
      "text": "and we become allies."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 817677.0,
      "end_time": 823148.0,
      "text": "So go away from your comfort into a bigger, brighter thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 823148.0,
      "end_time": 828140.0,
      "text": "because that is how we will stop another Ferguson from happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 828140.0,
      "end_time": 830370.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s how we create a community"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 830370.0,
      "end_time": 833382.0,
      "text": "where everybody, especially young black men, can thrive."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 833382.0,
      "end_time": 836305.0,
      "text": "So this last thing is going to be harder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 836305.0,
      "end_time": 839173.0,
      "text": "and I know it, but I&#39;m just going to put it out there anyway."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 839173.0,
      "end_time": 844412.0,
      "text": "When we see something, we have to have the courage to say something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 844412.0,
      "end_time": 848206.0,
      "text": "even to the people we love."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 848206.0,
      "end_time": 851847.0,
      "text": "You know, it&#39;s holidays and it&#39;s going to be a time"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 851847.0,
      "end_time": 855279.0,
      "text": "when we&#39;re sitting around the table and having a good time."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 855279.0,
      "end_time": 857478.0,
      "text": "Many of us, anyways, will be in holidays,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 857478.0,
      "end_time": 862402.0,
      "text": "and you&#39;ve got to listen to the conversations around the table."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 862402.0,
      "end_time": 869094.0,
      "text": "You start to say things like, &quot;Grandma&#39;s a bigot.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 869094.0,
      "end_time": 870924.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 870924.0,
      "end_time": 873863.0,
      "text": "&quot;Uncle Joe is racist.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 873863.0,
      "end_time": 878482.0,
      "text": "And you know, we love Grandma and we love Uncle Joe. We do."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 878482.0,
      "end_time": 885317.0,
      "text": "We know they&#39;re good people, but what they&#39;re saying is wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 885317.0,
      "end_time": 892300.0,
      "text": "And we need to be able to say something, because you know who else is at the table?"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 892300.0,
      "end_time": 895154.0,
      "text": "The children are at the table."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 895154.0,
      "end_time": 900399.0,
      "text": "And we wonder why these biases don&#39;t die, and move from generation to generation?"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 900399.0,
      "end_time": 903650.0,
      "text": "Because we&#39;re not saying anything."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 903650.0,
      "end_time": 910172.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve got to be willing to say, &quot;Grandma, we don&#39;t call people that anymore.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 910172.0,
      "end_time": 915383.0,
      "text": "&quot;Uncle Joe, it isn&#39;t true that he deserved that."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 915383.0,
      "end_time": 918319.0,
      "text": "No one deserves that.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 918319.0,
      "end_time": 921733.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ve got to be willing"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 921733.0,
      "end_time": 926507.0,
      "text": "to not shelter our children from the ugliness of racism"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 926507.0,
      "end_time": 929819.0,
      "text": "when black parents don&#39;t have the luxury to do so,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 929819.0,
      "end_time": 934600.0,
      "text": "especially those who have young black sons."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 934600.0,
      "end_time": 937981.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve got to take our lovely darlings, our future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 937981.0,
      "end_time": 945783.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;ve got to tell them we have an amazing country with incredible ideals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 945783.0,
      "end_time": 948762.0,
      "text": "we have worked incredibly hard, and we have made some progress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 948762.0,
      "end_time": 951932.0,
      "text": "but we are not done."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 951932.0,
      "end_time": 955926.0,
      "text": "We still have in us this old stuff"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 955926.0,
      "end_time": 958967.0,
      "text": "about superiority and it is causing us"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 958967.0,
      "end_time": 962439.0,
      "text": "to embed those further into our institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 962439.0,
      "end_time": 964418.0,
      "text": "and our society and generations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 964418.0,
      "end_time": 968027.0,
      "text": "and it is making for despair"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 968027.0,
      "end_time": 975151.0,
      "text": "and disparities and a devastating devaluing of young black men."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 975151.0,
      "end_time": 977612.0,
      "text": "We still struggle, you have to tell them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 977612.0,
      "end_time": 980390.0,
      "text": "with seeing both the color"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 980390.0,
      "end_time": 984024.0,
      "text": "and the character of young black men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 984024.0,
      "end_time": 987857.0,
      "text": "but that you, and you expect them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 987857.0,
      "end_time": 992371.0,
      "text": "to be part of the forces of change in this society"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 992371.0,
      "end_time": 998939.0,
      "text": "that will stand against injustice and is willing, above all other things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 998939.0,
      "end_time": 1008705.0,
      "text": "to make a society where young black men can be seen for all of who they are."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 1008710.0,
      "end_time": 1013632.0,
      "text": "So many amazing black men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 1013630.0,
      "end_time": 1021962.0,
      "text": "those who are the most amazing statesmen that have ever lived,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 1021960.0,
      "end_time": 1024993.0,
      "text": "brave soldiers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 1024990.0,
      "end_time": 1029284.0,
      "text": "awesome, hardworking laborers."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 1029290.0,
      "end_time": 1033946.0,
      "text": "These are people who are powerful preachers."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 1033940.0,
      "end_time": 1039535.0,
      "text": "They are incredible scientists and artists and writers."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 1039540.0,
      "end_time": 1043515.0,
      "text": "They are dynamic comedians."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 1043510.0,
      "end_time": 1048446.0,
      "text": "They are doting grandpas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 1048450.0,
      "end_time": 1051482.0,
      "text": "caring sons."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 1051480.0,
      "end_time": 1056237.0,
      "text": "They are strong fathers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 1056240.0,
      "end_time": 1060596.0,
      "text": "and they are young men with dreams of their own."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 1060590.0,
      "end_time": 1064147.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 1064150.0,
      "end_time": 1074150.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}